In [58]:
file_name = "./bulk.airflow.downloaded_1min.parquet.ohlcv.futures.v7.ccxt.binance.v1_0_0"
schema = None
partitioning = ds.partitioning(schema, flavor="hive")
dataset = pq.ParquetDataset(
    # Replace URI with path.
    file_name,
    #filesystem=filesystem,
    #filters=filters,
    partitioning=partitioning,
    use_legacy_dataset=False,
)
# To read also the index we need to use `read_pandas()`, instead of
# `read_table()`.
# See https://arrow.apache.org/docs/python/parquet.html#reading-and-writing-single-files.
columns = None
table = dataset.read_pandas(columns=columns)
df = table.to_pandas()

Calculating Close-Close Price Differences¶

In [59]:
split_dfs = {i: None for i in df['currency_pair'].unique()}

# 1
for curr in df['currency_pair'].unique():
    split_dfs[curr] = df[df['currency_pair'] == curr]

# 2
for pair, frame in split_dfs.items():
    close_price = frame['close']
    time_diff = frame['timestamp']
    close_change = [None] + [(close_price[i] - close_price[i - 1]) / (time_diff[i] - time_diff[i - 1]) for i in range(1, len(close_price))]
    frame['close_change'] = close_change

# 3
for pair, frame in split_dfs.items():
    frame['normalized_close_change'] = (frame['close_change'] - frame['close_change'].mean()) / frame['close_change'].std()

Normalized Price Change Plots¶

In [60]:
sns.set_style("darkgrid")
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(12, 6)})

for pair, frame in split_dfs.items():
    sns.histplot(x=frame['normalized_close_change'], bins=range(-10, 11, 1)).set(title=pair)
    plt.axvline(-3, color='firebrick')
    plt.axvline(3, color='firebrick')
    plt.show()

The red lines indicate bounds for $3$ standard deviations from the mean price difference.

Exporting Outlier Price Change Data¶

In [61]:
split_outlier_dfs = {pair: split_dfs[pair][abs(split_dfs[pair]['normalized_close_change']) > 3] for pair in split_dfs.keys()}

for pair, frame in split_outlier_dfs.items():
    frame.to_csv("./output/{0}.csv".format(pair))
